{"tid":300436,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"【愛國愛港】政府建議白米鎘含量放寬","createTime":"2017-06-28T01:48:15.000Z","updateTime":"2017-06-28T04:02:43.000Z","uid":23707,"like":1,"dislike":6,"uniUserReply":0,"replies":[{"pid":"5cbf88c92411ee5063f5440b4af2b701e851f94a","tid":300436,"uid":23707,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T01:48:16.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"http://hk.apple.nextmedia.com/news/art/20170607/20047308\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fhk.apple.nextmedia.com%2Fnews%2Fart%2F20170607%2F20047308&d=AWFfUEWSyAy1hQVEKdBgyAIBMskQiLF9ooRt%2FFIrCZo%3D&h=75073800\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=http%3A%2F%2Fhk.apple.nextmedia.com%2Fnews%2Fart%2F20170607%2F20047308&h=a2408496\" target=\"_blank\">http://hk.apple.nextmedia.com/news/art/20170607/20047308</a><br />\n<br />\n【本報訊】政府新建議下，有6項食物金屬含量標準會較現時放寬。其中，市民主要食糧精米（白米），現時鎘最高准許含量每公斤0.1毫克，當局建議放寬至0.2毫克，與中國、韓國、新加坡及歐盟相同，但較法典的0.4毫克低。政府消息人士相信，規格放寬後，內地米供港有機會增加。<br />\n免世貿成員國挑戰<br />\n消息人士解釋，香港為世界貿易組織成員，任何更改要以國際標準為原則，若用較國際嚴謹的鎘上限需要解釋，否則其他成員國會挑戰。<br />\n食物法典委員會現時白米標準是每公斤0.4毫克，但由於港人食米比較多，風險較高，標準要定得較國際高，再參考中國、韓國等地，決定放寬至0.2毫克，「如果要維持0.1毫克，除非你解釋到香港食米量超過日韓歐盟，否則其他成員國會挑戰我哋」。他認同以往不合格白米，未來有機會入口本港，但即使放寬標準，一般食用量並不會出現健康問題。<span style=\"color: green;\">食安中心資料顯示，長期攝入鎘可損害腎功能，亦可能致癌。</span><br />\n<br />\n另外，捕獵魚類例如深海魚，現時將所有形態的汞（水銀）含量綜合計算，但新標準只會計算毒性最強的甲基汞，其他形態水銀不會規管。消息指，國際最關注的為甲基汞，因其毒性較高，孕婦攝取有機會影響胎兒健康，法典亦只規管甲基汞。其餘放寬的包括葉菜類蔬菜及小麥的鎘含量，以及罐裝食物的錫含量。"},{"pid":"5f16946e8d83d5c0a7befd70f087dfe55e7f8af8","tid":300436,"uid":107623,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T01:55:07.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"07ab49bcadfb1979eebe0b1cf471743f4d4fd510","tid":300436,"uid":55913,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T02:18:57.000Z","msg":"係啦 食啦 無害既"},{"pid":"569a95f646a5718123a36e403f1a93c9e94f3ce7","tid":300436,"uid":30569,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T02:22:13.000Z","msg":"因為港人嘅抗毒性比起蝗要差<br />\n所以用呢招去毒殺港人<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"655bcb15e771210f77686538b314493e1dc3e9d7","tid":300436,"uid":113073,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T02:23:32.000Z","msg":"除左傷腎，仲有骨質疏鬆。 Google「痛痛病」<br />\n<br />\n致癌好似冇話好直接，唔記得有冇直接性<br />\n<br />\n不過呢隻重金屬生物累積性較強，會取代鈣吸收導致骨質疏鬆。<br />\n<br />\n食物重金屬限制梗係嚴d好，挑咩戰<img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/01.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"30d23627b151a799c2d3a9feb1ddd9dda1bacfed","tid":300436,"uid":64047,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T02:23:45.000Z","msg":"蚹蛤蟈蜻"},{"pid":"607b3ab1c46bbac9260bcb174c9068cffb7d44fa","tid":300436,"uid":28654,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T02:24:30.000Z","msg":"以毒攻獨<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"93e5502c74dc4be1b12514d98f57937316b21532","tid":300436,"uid":20856,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T03:18:23.000Z","msg":"食日本米食輻射都唔會食支那米<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d42f89aed825edaad2823b8c0ee534e472062fb8","tid":300436,"uid":53223,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T03:20:37.000Z","msg":"以後唔好再食飯<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a6cb1c0512c9c7b88f32e7603394195510f9c1b1","tid":300436,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T03:52:33.000Z","msg":"Economist早幾星期先講支那農地有幾正<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\nIn 2014 the government published a national soil survey which showed that 16.1% of all soil and 19.4% of farmland was contaminated by organic and inorganic chemical pollutants and by metals such as lead, cadmium and arsenic......<br />\n<br />\n.......<strong>Cadmium and arsenic were found in 40% of the affected land</strong>. Officials say that 35,000 square kilometres of farmland is so polluted that no agriculture should be allowed on it at all.<br />\n<br />\n ......In 2002 China&rsquo;s ministry of agriculture conducted one of the few nationwide food tests to look for such heavy metals; <span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">it found that 28% of the rice samples it took had excess lead and 10% had excess cadmium</span></span><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.economist.com/news/briefing/21723128-and-fixing-it-will-be-hard-and-costly-most-neglected-threat-public-health-china\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fnews%2Fbriefing%2F21723128-and-fixing-it-will-be-hard-and-costly-most-neglected-threat-public-health-china&d=AWFfUEWSyAy1hQVEKdBgyAIBMskQiLF9ooRt%2FFIrCZo%3D&h=9a10c5ce\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.economist.com/news/briefing/21723128-and-fixing-it-will-be-hard-and-costly-most-neglected-threat-public-health-china</a>"},{"pid":"03205430f12b1e05b64ca77d611d8735edfeb44e","tid":300436,"uid":43009,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T04:01:26.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>以後唔好再食飯<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n其實真係唔好食咁多白米<br />\n食咁多精製澱粉冇益，gi又高<br />\n要食就食低gi食物，燕麥、糙米嗰啲<br />\n高纖、健康啲，又減到肥"},{"pid":"81d823ee864970e04c25e6362e4d4a67ce55a3c7","tid":300436,"uid":49392,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-28T04:02:43.000Z","msg":"出街唔好食米啦"}]}